This code solves the "Surrounded Regions" problem, which flips all 'O' regions completely surrounded by 'X' to 'X' while leaving 'O' regions connected to the boundary unchanged. 
It uses BFS starting from boundary cells: first, all 'O's on the four borders are marked as '#' (temporary marker) and enqueued. 
Then BFS propagates from these boundary 'O's to mark all connected 'O's as '#' (these are the ones not surrounded). 
Finally, it scans the entire board: any remaining 'O' (unmarked) is truly surrounded and flipped to 'X', while all '#' markers are converted back to 'O'.

Time Complexity: O(m × n) - each cell is processed at most once.
Space Complexity: O(m × n) - for the queue in the worst case (e.g., entire board filled with 'O's connected to the boundary).

import java.util.*;
class Solution {
    public void solve(char[][] board){
        int m = board.length;
        int n = board[0].length;
        Queue<int[]> q = new LinkedList<>();
        for(int i = 0; i < m; i++){
            if(board[i][0] == 'O') {
                board[i][0] = '#';
                q.offer(new int[]{i, 0});
            }
            if(board[i][n-1] == 'O') {
                board[i][n-1] = '#';
                q.offer(new int[]{i, n-1});
            }
        }
        for(int j = 0; j < n; j++){
            if(board[0][j] == 'O'){
                board[0][j] = '#';
                q.offer(new int[]{0, j});
            }
            if(board[m-1][j] == 'O'){
                board[m-1][j] = '#';
                q.offer(new int[]{m-1, j});
            }
        }
        int[][] dir = {{0,-1},{0,1},{1,0},{-1,0}};
        while(!q.isEmpty()) {
            int[] curr = q.poll();
            int row = curr[0];
            int col = curr[1];
            for(int[] d : dir){
                int nr = row + d[0];
                int nc = col + d[1];
                if(nr >= 0 && nr < m && nc >= 0 && nc < n && board[nr][nc] == 'O'){
                    board[nr][nc] = '#';
                    q.offer(new int[]{nr,nc});
                }
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0; i<m; i++){
            for(int j = 0 ; j<n; j++){
                if(board[i][j] == 'O'){
                    board[i][j] = 'X';
                }
                else if(board[i][j] == '#'){
                    board[i][j] = 'O';
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
